description: Six minutes and twenty six seconds are enough to realize that I live in chaos, or not, maybe I just realized how strange life feels when you question what I am questioning, it sounds pretty good to want to live an interesting life but it is complicated to assimilate the risks of accepting chaos, it sounds ugly to not be able to live that false peace again, but nothing sounds worse and more disillusioning in the first place than knowing that all that is known as peace is only the result of denying chaos, comfort is nothing more than a thought that shapes and simplifies the meaning of denying chaos, it is only a feeling of rest, which I prefer to call a slow and imperceptible agony that in simple words makes your life become shorter and shorter, the fish will not live more than ten minutes if it remains without being in a sea in chaos....
